(Constraint
    "Persona-spirit must not contain import logic for existing intent/*.nota files. Spirit's contract, daemon, and storage are for typed psyche-statement records going forward; the legacy file substrate is not spirit's concern. If a one-time migration of existing .nota content is wanted later, it is a dumb separate tool that calls spirit's normal Record operation through the CLI like any other agent — never a spirit-internal feature, never a special contract verb, never an ingestion mode, never an import-aware code path inside spirit. The default approach is to let agents re-log content by hand as it becomes relevant. A separate tool is only built if the psyche explicitly asks for it; otherwise hand-relogging is the path."
    "importing existing nota files *STAYS THE FUCK OUT OF SPIRIT* - we can make a dumb tool for a one-time import if we feel like it, but we might just get an agent to re-log everything by hand. DO NOT INTRODUCE IMPORT LOGIC IN SPIRIT!"
