(Clarification
    "persona-introspect is itself a persona component and the universal Tap/Untap mandate applies to it equally. The signal-persona-introspect contract must include the observable block; persona-introspect daemon must accept Tap/Untap subscriptions and emit OperationReceived / EffectEmitted events like every other persona component. The fact that introspect's primary role is consuming other components' Tap streams does not exempt it from being itself observable — meta-introspection (an introspect subscriber observing introspect itself) is the right shape."
    "of course! debug the debugger!"
    "Psyche closing the /257 §4 Q2 ambiguity. The universal Tap/Untap mandate (component-shape.nota 2026-05-20T02:00:00Z) applies to persona-introspect with no exception. The 'debug the debugger' framing is the load-bearing principle: a tool that observes other tools must itself be observable."
    Maximum
    2026-05-21T10:00:00Z)
